National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and Japan's National Security Secretariat Secretary General Akiba Takeo spoke about regional security and U.S.-Japan bilateral cooperation. They discussed the recent improvement in Japan-Republic of Korea relations and expressed support for Prime Minister Kishida's visit to Kyiv. Sullivan thanked Prime Minister Kishida for his successful visit to India and reaffirming Japan's commitment to a free and open Indo-Pacific. They also emphasized the importance of supporting Ukraine in its defense against Russia's invasion and maintaining a credible deterrence capability. Both officials pledged to deepen the bilateral partnership to advance their shared vision for the Indo-Pacific.